hter, she brought an au pair girl down with her from London you know, to look after the baby. And I said to her - to - her mother, to Molly, I said, you know, I said, I was an au pair girl only thirteen. That woman next to us was going to have a baby, and
 
she had - had a - had a - two others besides, and I says - and my mother - she says to my mother - let me have Edith Mrs Clark - Mrs Rhys, she said, while I'm - in bed. Oh, my mother said, her father wouldn't be willing, she's too young, she said, to do t
h
at. None of the others have done nothing, well of course there was - four older than me see. And she said - oh, come on, she's so tidy, she said, I'll have her, she said. Well, she said, I'll ask her father - but my mother didn't ask my father, 'cos my fa
ther didn't - trouble you know. But he wasn't willing for me - to do it, because he said to my father - to my mother, what are you going to put Edith now, she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16019800\charrsid12156020 
wasn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020  to go nursing, he said, but I don't know how to go about it. So I often say I was born fift
y years too soon. Yes. Now - you've got every chance to go haven't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
They were willing for you to go really were there, it was just that you didn't know how to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 No. Well I told her - that's we used to do, I said to her, I've found out m
am I said to her. You go to - you know {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Mount Pleasant{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 hospital they call now, they called that the work house then, and you had to go and scrub and things for a year, and study and they teach you then. That's what you used to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 But you couldn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
So - my mother said she didn't know how. Well now you know, the - you - if you want a favour - they go to councilors now you know and they do it for you. Well of course then if my mother knew councillors then - perhaps they could have had me, but yo
u know, there wasn't such - much call then, there was no hospitals to be had you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 So you went in to help this lady next door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
My - I - my mother was calling me at seven every morning. And I was only thirteen. And - I - he was - the man w
as lighting the fire, see Mr Rayburn, he was lighting the fire for me every morning, and I was going in. I was picking up the two children, and I was dressing them, giving them breakfast, taking them to school. Sending them to school. The school was only 
just over the road and down the hill a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16019800\charrsid12156020 little way}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
, not on the main road at all. Well then I used to - go up to her then, take a pan of water and a brush and comb for her to brush her hair and see - I wash her hands and face. I used to tidy the - I'd make he
r breakfast then, I used to tidy the bed - bath - the bed - the bedroom all, and the childrens bedroom, the landing, the stairs, I used to clean all the front then - before the doctor came. And the doctor used to tell her, your place is shining lovely dow
n there. I know it is, she said. Well then - after dinner I - oh after dinner then, I'd ask her what was she doing - having for dinner, my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16019800\charrsid12156020 mother\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020  come in then, to help me to do the dinner and see that they had - the children had their dinner, she had it. 
Well then, she - I - the children was going back to school then. I'd clean the kitchen then, and the glass house. And then my mother would show me then how to wash the nappies. Yes. Put me on a stool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 And you'd left school then had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 No. The 
Boardman came. And my mother said, you're the only one that the board man - and my sister was teaching then, the one older than me, she had teaching in Plas Mall school, and my mother - she said to my mother, I don't like it mam, she said, that Edith is n
e
xt door, she said, she's supposed to be in school 'til she's fourteen she said. Well I can't have her to go, she said, she's gone in next door, she said. So this school - this school - the school mistress said then, oh doesn't matter Catherine, she said, 
d
on't worry, we'll put it all right, she said. But my - and the Boardman came. And he said to my mother, where's that girl you've got, in Welsh you know. Go in there and talk to her, she is next door, she said, she is looking after the woman in bed, she sa
id. The old man would knock me then - knock at the door, and he had one arm all - old Bowen his name was, and he said, how are you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16019800\charrsid12156020 M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 itching, he said, to me in Welsh. Well, I am coming in to do a favour for Mrs Abram. Favour, he said, you'll have jail. So off he went then. I went back to school after
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 How long did you do it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 For what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 How long did you go in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Three weeks. And then going in - in every night to nurse the baby for her then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did you get paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Nothing thank you 
very much. Oh - they did not pay then, see they didn't have it to do, to give. Well you know, then you'd have neighbours then, you haven't got 'em today, no. No, you'd have neighbours then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes I did. Yes. I used to knock peopl
e's doors if they had a baby for me to go and nurse. Yes. I was so fond of children. Yes. There's little girl by here now, she's going sixteen, and I said to her mother, oh there's good for nothing, I said, Ann is, I said, you'll be sorry I said, you make
 
her help you, I said, she's out working. And then the girl gallivanted and going to play - with a - with all - with the child next door. I said, she's old enough now I said to do something, and I often throw that up you know. I was looking after a woman w
i
th other two children when I was only thirteen. Yes. So my father said to me, so - so my mother - well now what are we going to put her in, he said. So - a man in the same street then - came to fetch me, his wife was bad. I was in there then for a couple 
of weeks again. But she was giving me sixpence a week. And after that then, my - my elder sister was a dressmaker, and she said, oh you'd better put her to something else, mam, she said, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16019800\charrsid12156020 she\rquote ll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020  learn with me, she said. So my mother put me to learn, and I ha
d my trade. And I was going to - to sew, when I was - fifteen - not fifteen, sixteen. No, when I was - I went in February - and I would be - sixteen in the May. And I finished my trade - when I was eighteen. And I'm sewing ever since. Yes. And I - I serve
d an apprenticeship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
When you were a little girl living at Berkely Terrace did you - did the older children help the younger children with things they found difficult, like dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 No, we were playing and dressing up one another you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
You wouldn't help one another, the older children did they help the younger children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
No, well of course - we were not much between us do you see. Only two years -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 There were only about two years between you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes. So we w
ere all together, just the same size the youngest ones you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did the younger children help the older in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
No. Oh yes, my sister the one that was in school, she used to help my mother a lot you know. She used to wash the nappies - for the - for the youngest but one that was born. Yes. Yes. And she used to walk to the higher grade in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Swansea{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Well they didn't have it you see, the money was small then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were in school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Oh
 yes, my mother was putting us all to bed, yes. She was washing us, she was putting us in the scullery, sit on the table, washing our legs and washing our hands and necks and - and faces and then she said you won't have much in the morning then to do. Eve
ry night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did anyone else put you to bed besides your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
No, only ourselves then. But my - but my father used to come in every night I remember him, to tuck us up. Not for us to roll out. Yes. Used to come up every night then, before he'd go
 to bed he'd come in and tuck us up, yes. Yes. Oh when we were bad you know - my father - used to make all sorts of medicine for us. Yes. I remember him once - he had a - a white turnip, and used to scoop it you know, a big hole in it, and put - candy sug
a
r in it, and he'd put it on the hob. And - I don't remember - no, a Devonshire stove, I don't remember a fireplace with that, we had a big Devonshire stove in the kitchen, and a big square oven, and my mother used to - she used to weigh out about sixty po
und of flour twice a week. Yes. And she used to make - toal beren, she - we used to - buy - yeast to bake the bread. No. No. She used to bake the beren. And I remember used to make it - we had a big big iron }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15100470\charrsid12156020 saucepan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 , she'd scrub ten big potatoes, and she'd
 put - two cupful of hops in it, a cup of sugar - and - one of salt and perhaps two of sugar. And - put it to summer - until all them had mashed up you know, then she was washing her hands you know, and she was squeezing them altogether like you know, and
 she'd empty 'em out into a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15100470\charrsid12156020 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
 earthenware pan. And she'd leave it there then - oh no, she always kept - from the last lot she'd made - a bottle. Then when that was lukewarm - she'd pur it in then, into that you see, and then it would work. And then she used 
to strain it all and bottle it. It would last about ten weeks. Yes. That's a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 You'd use that then for a drink would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
No, no. That for the bread, to rise the bread. Yes. That's what she used. Beren Total they called it. Mm. Yes. My mother used to make that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did she make Diod Faen or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Pardon? She used to make pop, and stinging nettles and things in it you know. Yes. Well there was nothing else to drink 'cos - my father didn't drink at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 What age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Let me see. Oh I used to go to bed about twelve ourselves, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 You shared the bedroom you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 That's right, with our girls all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did you share a bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes, my two sisters used to sleep, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 In the scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Oh my father - my mother used to bath us sometimes twice a week. But if it was cold she'd have the - the big bath in front of the fire, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Oh every time they were dirty, yes. I remember having a pinafore as much as three or four times, but mind you had to take it off in the night, and fold it and put it to one side, it was lasting another day or two then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Oh in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 No, we never used another room for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Where did your mother cook?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Well it was - in the scullery doing it and coo
king in this big oven you know. Yes. No gas, no electric then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 A coal range was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Coal, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
And she had a big boiler - in the corner of the scullery you know. And - fire they used to call it in Welsh y
ou know, a copper boiler. She used to - boil all the clothes in there, boil everything then. And she used to soak them with Felsnaptha the night before. My mother used to soak them you know and then she used to wash them. And she had - we had a wooden - b
ench like at the back you know, ffwrwm we used to call it. Well then my mother'd bring that in the scullery, she'd put a bath or a tub - oh my father used to make tubs, we used to - my mother'd buy a cask you know, and my father'd burn it up, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16019800\charrsid12156020 outside}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020  the ga
rden there was a big field outside our garden, and my father would burn it all then you know, and - then - he'd - saw it half you know, and he would saw - saw it a bit lower then and it had two handles in it you know, and sometimes he'd make two iron hand
les and put them on the tub, and my mother used to dolly in them then. Yes. You know like a piece of - with four leg - four legs to it and dolly and I bought one when I got married five }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16019800\charrsid12156020 shillings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 , it's in the small cupboard now. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 People used to dolly didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Yes. That's right. No, my husband taught me. He said, you mustn't hit it, he said, you may - you mu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15100470\charrsid12156020 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 t turn it like that he said to me, to twist the clothes back and forth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 That's the principle of the washing machine really isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Yes. I've never had a washing machine. Gave me the dolly for blankets and things. And I washed - some of my blankets, they like veil is gone. And my mother said, you don't pound, I pound. She used to take it you know and I didn't. No. Yes. They s
ay - too much soap some say and too - but my mother said, no, I wouldn't use too much soap, I would be afraid to waste it, she said And some says hot - water too hot you know. But I don't, I use - hot or cold, you know - medium then in between. I don't st
udy what - the - how hot the water is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 When was breakfast eaten when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Oh - well my mother'd call us - say about - eight o'clock to half past and then she'd give us breakfast then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 What members of the family were present at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Well of course my sister, my eldest sister, she was going out to sew. Going up Port Talbot then you know, used to come to fetch you. But when it came my turn - my father said to my mother, Edith is not going out - to - sew about the houses
. No, my mother said, she's not going to - she's got the middle room, she said, to do it. And my father always said - that that's what my eldest sister ill. Different food with people, not cooked and things properly you know. My father was very careful li
ke that with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 He would have breakfast before you children would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Oh my father was - my mother was get - would get up - about five o'clock. Then she'd call - my father would get up then. He was - going to work then by six. Well then - she'd 
go back to bed then. And she'd get up then again at seven. Well then she'd start making breakfast. And dressing us you know, and of course the older ones then - was doing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16019800\charrsid12156020 it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020  themselves you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Would your father have a meal then, or what would he have to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Oh - well it all depends. Jam sometimes. And my mother'd boil an egg, and she'd cut half each for us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Would your father have the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
No, only a cup of tea before he went. My father wasn't a big eater, no more than myself. Nor my husband wasn't a big eater. Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 What did you usually have to drink at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Oh tea - yes. Because I didn't like milk in my tea nor - nor my brothers like my - milk or sugar. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did you have anything different on c
ertain days for breakfast, like on a Sunday would you have something different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
No, my mother wouldn't cook on a Sunday. 'Cos we were going to chapel on the Sunday morning. But of course we had a dinner when we was coming back you know. Nor my mother
 didn't make any elevenses, nothing like that. You had a meal and it - in its style, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
What about midday meals in the weekday, how many of you would be there for midday meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Oh - only my brother, and my two younger sisters and me. T
he others would be - out you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 What would you have to eat midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Oh my mother would make a dinner. Say she'd buy - a - beef - beef pieces and things you know and make a pie for us. And boil potatoes and things. Well then another day, she'd make }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15100470\charrsid12156020 broth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
. And then for tea we'd have dumplings with apple dumplings and things. And fish and things. We had plenty to eat you know. According to what they could afford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Would you have anything different on Sundays or any other day, special days
?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 No, we had - we'd have a hot dinner, and then mother on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16019800\charrsid12156020  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
a Saturday afternoon, she'd make a - as much as six tarts. Yes. And always cleaned the potatoes. Everything like that ready for Sunday. -Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 What about after then, you had breakfast, you
 had a midday meal, what would be the other meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Tea. Yes. My mother'd have tart for us then and things see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Would you have another meal again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes, we'd have supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 What would you have for supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Well whatever you wanted. Sh
e'd have cold meat for you see and she'd always put - the remains of the dinner in to warm. Just before we would go to chapel and if you wanted that you'll have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 What about in the weekday, would you have supper in the weekday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes. Well - perhaps she'd make us toast something like that you know. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 What did you have to drink then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
Oh only tea. Yes, or my mother'd make pop. We - I didn't like milk. No. No milk. And my mother brought us all up on the breast see. Yes. All of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Everyone of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Every one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 You mentioned that your mother baked her own bread?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Your father didn't do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did your mother make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 No, my mother didn't make that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did she bake the bread in her own house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
No. And when we - when we came bigger - and you know - she was tired, she used to - we used to take it down to - the baker in Plas Mall, and perhaps we'd have eight or nine loa
ves coming. Oh - and then we'd be picking the - and my mother said, who has been picking this loaf?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 It's lovely hot like that isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes, she bottled fruit. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did she bottle any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 
No, she didn't bottle - I've done a lot of it in my time, yes, and pickled eggs
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Would your mother make any pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes, she used to make pickled onions and pickled cabbage, I remember that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Did she make any wine or medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 No. 
No. My father'd make a lot of medicines. Yes. Because if he had - he says - you know, when we had worms - he was going to the garden, you - wermod. And we used to have tea wermod. And he used to wash it, used to put it in a jug, pour boil - pour boiling w
ater over it and let it simmer there, and you had to drink that then. Oh he looked after our health you know, more than anything. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 He was clever like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1400613 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Yes, he was. Oh my father was a bit of a doctor, no end of }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15100470\charrsid12156020 neihbours}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020  would come after him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11172311 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10514204\charrsid12156020 Was any beer brewed for the family?
