er'd buy a ham you know now when say when - she was going to have a baby, going - to be confined, her sister would come down to look after - my mother'd always buy a cauldron of butter they used to call it, and she used to stock it like you know, during t
h
e time that she was upstairs. And my father wouldn't let my mother get up 'til after the tenth day. Now they bring you up - there was a woman the other - oh - it was on the paper this week now, that there was a woman that confine - had been - had a baby, 
and she - the baby was strangled in Cardiff. Do you see? Found in Cardiff. Well - and they said - that the woman wants - seeing to you know, and my father said, there was no woman ought to go out under ten days. Yes. He always said that.
